\u01d2 (\u00f4) / \u00e2 (\u00e2) <br/> \u0432\u00f4\u043b\u043a/v\u00f4lk \u0432\u00e2\u043b\u043a/v\u00e2lk\n| \u043e (\u0254), \u044a (\u0259) (Solun region) <br/> \u0432\u043e\u043b\u043a/volk <br/> \u0432\u044a\u043b\u043a/v\u0103lk\n| \u0103/\u044a (\u0259) <br/> \u0432\u044a\u043b\u043a/v\u0103lk\n| \u043e (\u0254) <br/> \u0432\u043e\u043b\u043a/volk\n| \u0103/\u044a (\u0259) <br/> \u0432\u044a\u043b\u043a/v\u0103lk\n|}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Slavs in Greece]]\n* [[Slavic-speakers of Greek Macedonia]]\n* [[Eastern South Slavic]]\n* [[Pomak language]]\n* [[Fallmerayer's Greek theory]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* [[Peter Trudgill|Trudgill P.]] (2000) \"Greece and European Turkey: From Religious to Linguistic Identity\" in ''Language and Nationalism in Europe'' (Oxford : Oxford University Press)\n* Iakovos D. Michailidis (1996) \"Minority Rights and Educational Problems in Greek Interwar Macedonia: The Case of the Primer 'Abecedar'\". Journal of Modern Greek Studies'' 14.2 329-343 [http://www.macedonian-heritage.gr/downloads/library/Michai01.pdf]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.oshchima.com/DBOOK/dictionary_-_text.pdf Dialectial dictionary of the Oschima speech of the Lerin dialect]\n\n{{Slavic languages}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Slavic Dialects Of Greece}}\n[[Category:Bulgarian language]]\n[[Category:Macedonian language]]\n[[Category:Languages of Greece]]\n", "name_user": "Jingiby", "label": "safe", "comment": "Small fix.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slavic_dialects_of_Greece"}
{"title_page": "Presidential National Guard (Tajikistan)", "text_new": "{{Infobox military unit\n| unit_name = Presidential National Guard\n| image = File:Presidential National Guardsman.jpg\n| caption = Members of the ceremonial company of the National Guard at the [[Palace of Nations, Dushanbe|Palace of Nations]] in [[Dushanbe]].\n| dates = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|1992|12|14}}\n| country = {{flag|Tajikistan}}\n| allegiance = [[File:Flag of the President of Tajikistan.svg|25px]] [[President of Tajikistan]]\n| branch = [[Tajik National Army]] (1992\u20132006) \n| type = National guard, special operations\n| role = \n| size = \n| command_structure = \n| garrison = [[Rasht District]], [[Dushanbe]]\n| garrison_label = \n| nickname = National Guard\n| patron = \n| motto = \"Service to the Country and the President's Life!\" (''\u0411\u0430 \u0412\u0430\u0442\u0430\u043d \u0441\u043e\u0434\u0438\u049b\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0445\u0438\u0437\u043c\u0430\u0442 \u043c\u0435\u043a\u0443\u043d\u0430\u043c!'')<ref>http://jumhuriyat.tj/index.php?art_id=20591</ref>\n| colors = {{color box|Red}} {{color box|Grey}} Red & Grey\n| colors_label = \n| march = \n| mascot = \n| equipment = \n| equipment_label = \n| battles = [[Tajik civil war]]\n| anniversaries = 3 September (Day of the National Guard/\u0420\u04ef\u0437\u0438 \u0413\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0438\u044f\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u0438)<ref>http://freedom.tj/2018/09/03/ruzi-gvardiyai-millii-jumhurii-tojikiston-muborak/</ref>\n| decorations = \n| battle_honours = \n| battle_honours_label = \n| disbanded = \n| flying_hours = \n| website = <!-- Commanders -->\n| commander1 = [[Emomali Rahmon]]\n| commander1_label = Supreme Commander in Chief\n| commander2 = Colonel Bobojon Jamolzoda<ref name=\"news\">{{cite web|url=https://news.tj/en/news/tajikistan/power/20131120/colonel-jamolzoda-appointed-commander-tajik-national-guard|title=Colonel Jamolzoda appointed commander of Tajik National Guard &#124; Tajikistan News ASIA-Plus|website=news.tj|accessdate=2018-09-27}}</ref>\n| commander2_label = \n| commander3 = \n| commander3_label = \n| commander4 = \n| commander4_label = \n| notable_commanders = {{bulleted list|[[Mahmud Khudoiberdiyev]]|[[Ghaffor Mirzoyev]]}}\n<!-- Insignia -->| identification_symbol = \n| identification_symbol_label = \n| identification_symbol_2 = \n| identification_symbol_2_label = \n| identification_symbol_3 = \n| identification_symbol_3_label = \n| identification_symbol_4 = \n| identification_symbol_4_label = <!-- Aircraft -->\n| aircraft_attack = \n| aircraft_bomber = \n| aircraft_electronic = \n| aircraft_fighter = \n| aircraft_helicopter = \n| aircraft_helicopter_attack = \n| aircraft_helicopter_cargo = \n| aircraft_helicopter_multirole = \n| aircraft_helicopter_observation = \n| aircraft_helicopter_transport = \n| aircraft_helicopter_trainer = \n| aircraft_helicopter_utility = \n| aircraft_interceptor = \n| aircraft_patrol = \n| aircraft_recon = \n| aircraft_trainer = \n| aircraft_transport = \n| aircraft_tanker = \n| native_name = \u0413\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0438\u044f\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u04e3 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u04e3\n}}\n\nThe '''Presidential National Guard''', formerly called the '''Brigade of Special Mission''' and '''Presidential Guard''', also called the '''[[National Guard (disambiguation)|National Guard]]''', is a service branch of the [[Armed Forces of the Republic of Tajikistan]], under direct command of the [[President (government title)|President]] of Tajikistan. Their primary task is ensuring public safety and security, which is similar to the tasks of the [[Tajik Internal Troops]]. The national guard also takes part in ceremonial duties in Tajikistan.\n\n==History==\nFormed on December 4, 1992, it was originally a special forces unit known as the '''Brigade of Special Mission''' during the 16th session of the [[Supreme Assembly (Tajikistan)|Supreme Assembly of Tajikistan]], under the Tajik Interior Ministry.<ref>https://news.tj/en/news/tajikistan/power/20161014/232030</ref> During its first years, the Guard underwent serious testing, which earned the trust of the President and the people. It was the reason why President [[Emomali Rahmon]] changed its name from the Brigade of Special Mission to the '''Presidential Guard''' on January 17, 1995.<ref name=\"globalsecurity\">{{cite web|url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/centralasia/tajik-guard.htm|author=John Pike|title=Tajikistan - National Guard|website=globalsecurity.org|accessdate=2018-09-27}}</ref> \n\nWithin two years, four additional units were formed in the towns of [[Chkalovsk, Tajikistan|Chkalovsk]], [[Kalinin, Tajikistan|Kalinin]], and [[Obigarm]]. They had a similar structure to the rest of the military. Worthy of note is the honesty that the National Guard has exhibited. The Rapid Reaction Force, also called the First Brigade, under [[Colonel]] [[Mahmud Khudoiberdiyev]],<ref>Heathershaw, page 34.</ref> took part in the [[Tajik civil war]], as part of the Guard and the regular Army. It became one of the most effective fighting units within the Army, but picked a fight with the 11th Brigade. They defeated the 11th, and attempted to take the capital in November 1998,<ref>https://jamestown.org/program/uprising-quashed-in-tajikistan-further-cataclysms-expected/</ref> but were defeated by another Guard unit and street thugs armed with [[AK-47]]s. The colonel and his men fled into [[Uzbekistan]].<ref>https://www.rferl.org/a/confession-suggests-new-trust-in-tajik-uzbek-relations/29395390.html</ref>\n\nIn 2004, the chief of the Guard (as well as head of the [[Drug Control Agency]]), [[Ghaffor Mirzoyev]], was arrested for corruption and [[drug trafficking]]. On January 26, 2004, the Presidential Guard was transformed into the National Guard. During the inauguration of the President on November 18, 2006, the Guard received the honor of presenting the Tajik state symbols.<ref name=\"globalsecurity\"/>\n\nA [[Mil Mi-8]] of the Guard [[2010 Tajik National Guard Mi-8 crash|crashed]] on October 6, 2010, close to [[Ezgand]] and [[Tavildara]]. The helicopter was caught in power lines while attempting to land, causing it to crash, leaving no survivors. It is Tajikistan's worst aviation accident since 1997.<ref name=\"planecrashinfo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.planecrashinfo.com/2010/2010-37.htm|website=planecrashinfo.com|title=2010/2010-37|accessdate=2018-09-27}}</ref><ref name=\"globalsecurity\"/><ref>http://factmil.com/publ/strana/tadzhikistan/zakon_o_nacionalnoj_gvardii_respubliki_tadzhikistan/82-1-0-83</ref>\n\nIn 2013, the PNG was placed under the command of Major General Bobodzhon Dzhamolzoda.<ref>http://old.news.tj/en/node/214217</ref> On 2 October 2014, a [[military parade]] was dedicated to the founding of the National Guard.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.news.tj/en/news/military-parade-dedicated-national-guard-take-place-tajik-capital-october-13|title=Military parade dedicated to the National Guard to take place in the Tajik capital on October 13 {{!}} Tajikistan News ASIA-Plus|access-date=2017-09-02}}</ref>\n\n== Structure ==\nUnder the auspices of the National Guard, there are:\n\n*Department of Command Affairs\n*Department of War Training\n*Headquarters\n**Operations Department\n**Organization and Mobilization Department\n**Communications, Military and Security Service Division\n**Command Office\n**[[Military Band]] (\u043e\u0440\u043a\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438 \u0413\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0438\u044f\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u0438)\n*Department of Education\n**Patriotic Education Section  \n**Military Discipline Section \n**Section for the Prevention of Offenses\n**Section for Psychological Work\n*Department of Arms and Equipment\n*Center for Personnel Training\n*Aviation Division\n*Department of Finance\n*Medical Department\n*Central Hospital\n*Newspaper \"Rodmardon\"\n*Dilovaron ([[pop music]] ensemble)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Ministry of Defence (Tajikistan)]]\n* [[Tajik National Army]]\n* [[Tajik Air Force]]\n* [[Tajik Mobile Forces]]\n* [[Tajik Border Troops]]\n* [[Tajik Internal Troops]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* {{Cite book |last=Heathershaw |first=John |year=2009 |title=Post-Conflict Tajikistan: The Politics of Peacebuilding and the Emergence of Legitimate Order |publisher=Routledge}}\n\n{{commons category|Tajik Presidential National Guard}}\n\n[[Category:National Guard of Tajikistan]]\n[[Category:Guards of honour]]\n[[Category:1992 establishments in Tajikistan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox military unit\n| unit_name = Presidential National Guard\n| image = File:Presidential National Guardsman.jpg\n| caption = Members of the ceremonial company of the National Guard at the [[Palace of Nations, Dushanbe|Palace of Nations]] in [[Dushanbe]].\n| dates = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|1992|12|14}}\n| country = {{flag|Tajikistan}}\n| allegiance = [[File:Flag of the President of Tajikistan.svg|25px]] [[President of Tajikistan]]\n| branch = [[Tajik National Army]] (1992\u20132006) \n| type = National guard, special operations\n| role = \n| size = \n| command_structure = \n| garrison = [[Rasht District]], [[Dushanbe]]\n| garrison_label = \n| nickname = National Guard\n| patron = \n| motto = \"Service to the Country and the President's Life!\" (''\u0411\u0430 \u0412\u0430\u0442\u0430\u043d \u0441\u043e\u0434\u0438\u049b\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0445\u0438\u0437\u043c\u0430\u0442 \u043c\u0435\u043a\u0443\u043d\u0430\u043c!'')<ref>http://jumhuriyat.tj/index.php?art_id=20591</ref>\n| colors = {{color box|Red}} {{color box|Grey}} Red & Grey\n| colors_label = \n| march = \n| mascot = \n| equipment = \n| equipment_label = \n| battles = [[Tajik civil war]]\n| anniversaries = 3 September (Day of the National Guard/\u0420\u04ef\u0437\u0438 \u0413\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0438\u044f\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u0438)<ref>http://freedom.tj/2018/09/03/ruzi-gvardiyai-millii-jumhurii-tojikiston-muborak/</ref>\n| decorations = \n| battle_honours = \n| battle_honours_label = \n| disbanded = \n| flying_hours = \n| website = <!-- Commanders -->\n| commander1 = [[Emomali Rahmon]]\n| commander1_label = Supreme Commander in Chief\n| commander2 = Colonel Bobojon Jamolzoda<ref name=\"news\">{{cite web|url=https://news.tj/en/news/tajikistan/power/20131120/colonel-jamolzoda-appointed-commander-tajik-national-guard|title=Colonel Jamolzoda appointed commander of Tajik National Guard &#124; Tajikistan News ASIA-Plus|website=news.tj|accessdate=2018-09-27}}</ref>\n| commander2_label = \n| commander3 = \n| commander3_label = \n| commander4 = \n| commander4_label = \n| notable_commanders = {{bulleted list|[[Mahmud Khudoiberdiyev]]|[[Ghaffor Mirzoyev]]}}\n<!-- Insignia -->| identification_symbol = \n| identification_symbol_label = \n| identification_symbol_2 = \n| identification_symbol_2_label = \n| identification_symbol_3 = \n| identification_symbol_3_label = \n| identification_symbol_4 = \n| identification_symbol_4_label = <!-- Aircraft -->\n| aircraft_attack = \n| aircraft_bomber = \n| aircraft_electronic = \n| aircraft_fighter = \n| aircraft_helicopter = \n| aircraft_helicopter_attack = \n| aircraft_helicopter_cargo = \n| aircraft_helicopter_multirole = \n| aircraft_helicopter_observation = \n| aircraft_helicopter_transport = \n| aircraft_helicopter_trainer = \n| aircraft_helicopter_utility = \n| aircraft_interceptor = \n| aircraft_patrol = \n| aircraft_recon = \n| aircraft_trainer = \n| aircraft_transport = \n| aircraft_tanker = \n| native_name = \u0413\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0438\u044f\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u04e3 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u04e3\n}}\n\nThe '''Presidential National Guard''', formerly called the '''Brigade of Special Mission''' and '''Presidential Guard''', also called the '''[[National Guard (disambiguation)|National Guard]]''', is a service branch of the [[Armed Forces of the Republic of Tajikistan]], under direct command of the [[President (government title)|President]] of Tajikistan. Their primary task is ensuring public safety and security, which is similar to the tasks of the [[Tajik Internal Troops]]. The national guard also takes part in ceremonial duties in Tajikistan.\n\n==History==\nFormed on December 4, 1992, it was originally a special forces unit known as the '''Brigade of Special Mission''' during the 16th session of the [[Supreme Assembly (Tajikistan)|Supreme Assembly of Tajikistan]], under the Tajik Interior Ministry.<ref>https://news.tj/en/news/tajikistan/power/20161014/232030</ref> During its first years, the Guard underwent serious testing, which earned the trust of the President and the people. It was the reason why President [[Emomali Rahmon]] changed its name from the Brigade of Special Mission to the '''Presidential Guard''' on January 17, 1995.<ref name=\"globalsecurity\">{{cite web|url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/centralasia/tajik-guard.htm|author=John Pike|title=Tajikistan - National Guard|website=globalsecurity.org|accessdate=2018-09-27}}</ref> \n\nWithin two years, four additional units were formed in the towns of [[Chkalovsk, Tajikistan|Chkalovsk]], [[Kalinin, Tajikistan|Kalinin]], and [[Obigarm]]. They had a similar structure to the rest of the military. Worthy of note is the honesty that the National Guard has exhibited. The Rapid Reaction Force, also called the First Brigade, under [[Colonel]] [[Mahmud Khudoiberdiyev]],<ref>Heathershaw, page 34.</ref> took part in the [[Tajik civil war]], as part of the Guard and the regular Army. It became one of the most effective fighting units within the Army, but picked a fight with the 11th Brigade. They defeated the 11th, and attempted to take the capital in November 1998,<ref>https://jamestown.org/program/uprising-quashed-in-tajikistan-further-cataclysms-expected/</ref> but were defeated by another Guard unit and street thugs armed with [[AK-47]]s. The colonel and his men fled into [[Uzbekistan]].<ref>https://www.rferl.org/a/confession-suggests-new-trust-in-tajik-uzbek-relations/29395390.html</ref>\n\nIn 2004, the chief of the Guard (as well as head of the [[Drug Control Agency]]), [[Ghaffor Mirzoyev]], was arrested for corruption and [[drug trafficking]]. On January 26, 2004, the Presidential Guard was transformed into the National Guard. During the inauguration of the President on November 18, 2006, the Guard received the honor of presenting the Tajik state symbols.<ref name=\"globalsecurity\"/>\n\nA [[Mil Mi-8]] of the Guard [[2010 Tajik National Guard Mi-8 crash|crashed]] on October 6, 2010, close to [[Ezgand]] and [[Tavildara]]. The helicopter was caught in power lines while attempting to land, causing it to crash, leaving no survivors. It is Tajikistan's worst aviation accident since 1997.<ref name=\"planecrashinfo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.planecrashinfo.com/2010/2010-37.htm|website=planecrashinfo.com|title=2010/2010-37|accessdate=2018-09-27}}</ref><ref name=\"globalsecurity\"/><ref>http://factmil.com/publ/strana/tadzhikistan/zakon_o_nacionalnoj_gvardii_respubliki_tadzhikistan/82-1-0-83</ref>\n\nIn 2013, the PNG was placed under the command of Major General Bobodzhon Dzhamolzoda.<ref>http://old.news.tj/en/node/214217</ref> On 2 October 2014, a [[military parade]] was was dedicated to the founding of the National Guard.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.news.tj/en/news/military-parade-dedicated-national-guard-take-place-tajik-capital-october-13|title=Military parade dedicated to the National Guard to take place in the Tajik capital on October 13 {{!}} Tajikistan News ASIA-Plus|access-date=2017-09-02}}</ref>\n\n== Structure ==\nUnder the auspices of the National Guard, there are:\n\n*Department of Command Affairs\n*Department of War Training\n*Headquarters\n**Operations Department\n**Organization and Mobilization Department\n**Communications, Military and Security Service Division\n**Command Office\n**[[Military Band]] (\u043e\u0440\u043a\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438 \u0413\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0438\u044f\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u0438)\n*Department of Education\n**Patriotic Education Section  \n**Military Discipline Section \n**Section for the Prevention of Offenses\n**Section for Psychological Work\n*Department of Arms and Equipment\n*Center for Personnel Training\n*Aviation Division\n*Department of Finance\n*Medical Department\n*Central Hospital\n*Newspaper \"Rodmardon\"\n*Dilovaron ([[pop music]] ensemble)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Ministry of Defence (Tajikistan)]]\n* [[Tajik National Army]]\n* [[Tajik Air Force]]\n* [[Tajik Mobile Forces]]\n* [[Tajik Border Troops]]\n* [[Tajik Internal Troops]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* {{Cite book |last=Heathershaw |first=John |year=2009 |title=Post-Conflict Tajikistan: The Politics of Peacebuilding and the Emergence of Legitimate Order |publisher=Routledge}}\n\n{{commons category|Tajik Presidential National Guard}}\n\n[[Category:National Guard of Tajikistan]]\n[[Category:Guards of honour]]\n[[Category:1992 establishments in Tajikistan]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Duplicate word removed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Presidential_National_Guard_(Tajikistan)"}
