| channel                  = [[Geo Entertainment]]\n| released                 = \n}}\n\n'''''Deewangi''''' ({{trans|Madness}}) is a 2019 [[Pakistani dramas|Pakistani]] romantic drama television series, produced by [[Abdullah Kadwani]] and [[Asad Qureshi]] under [[7th Sky Entertainment]]. It started airing on [[Geo Entertainment]] from 18 December 2019. It has [[Danish Taimoor]] and [[Hiba Bukhari]] in leads.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailytimes.com.pk/512362/7th-sky-entertainments-deewangi-stars-danish-taimoor-and-hiba-bukhari-in-lead-roles/|title=7th Sky Entertainment's 'Deewangi' stars Danish Taimoor and Hiba Bukhari in lead roles|date=2019-12-03|website=Daily Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/579440-deewangi-to-go-on-air-later-this-year|title=Deewangi to go on air later this year|last=NewsBytes|first=|date=|website=The News International|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/544444-zoya-nasir-shares-details-of-her-next-drama-deewangi|title=Zoya Nasir shares details of her next drama, Deewangi|last=Shabbir|first=Buraq|date=|website=The News International|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jang.com.pk/news/707222-another-heart-touching-story-of-geo-deewangi|title=\u062c\u06cc\u0648 \u06a9\u06cc \u0627\u06cc\u06a9 \u0627\u0648\u0631 \u062f\u0644 \u0645\u0648\u06c1 \u0644\u06cc\u0646\u06d2 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u06cc \u06a9\u06c1\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u2019\u062f\u06cc\u0648\u0627\u0646\u06af\u06cc\u2018|last=|first=|date=|website=Daily Jang|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/578745-geo-s-new-serial-deewangi-all-set-to-win-hearts|title=Geo\u2019s new serial \u2018Deewangi\u2019 all set to win hearts|last=|first=|date=|website=The News|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nThe story is about poor girl Nageen and rich boy sultan who fall in love with this girl when he saw her in the bus as a bus hostess for the first time! This story extend that Nageen doesn't want to marry sultan. Sultan want to marry her. He enforce her in bus station for marriage, there she slap Sultan and sultan then Sultan disguise himself as a good person and cheat her. He kidnap nageen on the day when she is going to marry him. Now what is next?\nWill they both meet again? Will Nageen forgive Sultan? Will there next meeting be tragic one? No one know about that\n\n== Cast==\n*[[Danish Taimoor]] as Sultan Durrani<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/21-Dec-2019/deewangi-first-episode-wins-hearts-of-the-audience|title=\u2018Deewangi\u2019 first episode wins hearts of the audience|date=2019-12-20|website=The Nation|language=en|access-date=2019-12-21}}</ref>\n*[[Hiba Bukhari]] as Nageen\n*[[Zoya Nasir]] as ramsha \n*[[Ismat Zaidi]] as Bi Jaan\n*[[Mehmood Aslam]] as ramsha's father\n* [[Ali Abbas (actor)|Ali Abbas]] as haroon\n* Faiza Gillani as Nuzhat, Nageen's sister\n* Parveen Akbar as Nuzhat's mother-in-law\n* Noor Ul Hasan as Rashid; Nageen's brother-in-law\n* Humera Bano\n* Nida Mumtaz as ramsha's mother\n* Aiza Awan as haroon's sister\n*Anas Ali Imran as Fawad; Sultan's friend\n* Fahima Awan as Faryal, Nageen's colleague\n* Salma Shaheen as Faryal's mother\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{imdbtitle|tt11609990}}\n\n[[Category:2019 Pakistani television series debuts]]\n\n{{Pakistan-tv-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Pakistani television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Deewangi\n| image                    = \n| caption                  = \n| show_name_2              = \n| native_name              = \n| genre                    = \n| creator                  = \n| 